I can share some of our electrical documentation from this year. These are all part of a bigger doc which has robot pictures, so I can’t share the whole thing. The goal of the doc at large is to be the place to go for any wiring related questions, and to be useful while debugging, so logical diagrams are a big deal.

It includes:

A simple table which shows which high power PDH channels each motor connects to

The same kind of table for low power connections from the MPM and low power PDH channels

A diagram to go along with the low power table

Diagrams and tables for CAN bus

We also have drawings with connections overlayed onto screenshots of robot CAD to go with most of these.

We used excalidraw to create these drawings. We choose to use excalidraw because of how easy and intuitive it is to create really pretty pictures, but it is lacking in collaboration - you basically just have to share the files around, which is pretty annoying. You could achieve similar results with google drawings or similar.

We use AutoCAD LT for electrical schematics. You can get free education seats as part of an FRC team. We like introducing the students to software that they might find in the bigger world. Its pretty intuitive and there are lots of online resources. I have tried to attach some examples from 2023, we typically go with smaller subsection drawings that link together to make an overall larger picture.
2023 - EBD - 000 - Block Diagram - R2.pdf (108.3 KB)
2023 - ED - 100 - PDP - R1.pdf (105.6 KB)
2023 - ED - 310 - Claw - R0.pdf (98.8 KB)
